description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to recruit a band 6 specialist nurse into the IDT team at Leighton hospital. This position is essential in manging complex cases and reducing delayed transfers of care within the hospital setting. The IDT team work alongside external partners to progress complex packages of care, assessment for Nursing homes and packages of care for terminal patients. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;IDT are integral in sign posting to the correct service, alongside processing Fast track paperwork and assessments for continuing health care provision. Working within the discharge to assess model that has been successfully implemented into the trust and is now entering its next phase. Working closely with the Community single point of access team.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This role requires a qualified Nurse who has had experience in assessing and managing complex needs with an understanding of discharge processes.  Either within the hospital setting or community. &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
